Exploratory Data Analysis in Action - EDA: Number of attacks¶

In this section we explore the Arial Bombing Data Set and apply techniques referred to as Exploratory Data Analysis.

Research questions¶

@Number of attacks

  • Q1: How many attacks were launched between 1939 and 1945 over Europe?
  • Q2: Which Allied Force was responsible for the most of the attacks? Did this change over time?
  • Q3: Which Allied Force launched the most attacks against Germany?
  • Q4: Is there a seasonal pattern in the attacks against Germany (e.g. winter vs. summer)?
  • Q5: Which area experienced the highest number of attacks? Did the area change over time?

Q1: How many attacks were launched between 1939 and 1945 over Europe?

In [6]:
import geopandas as gpd
from shapely.geometry import Polygon
world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
poly_europe = gpd.GeoSeries([Polygon([(-27,33), (45,33), (45,73.5), (-27,73.5)])])
bb_europe = gpd.GeoDataFrame({'geometry': poly_europe})
# assign crs
bb_europe.crs = {'init':'epsg:4326'}
bb_europe

europe = gpd.overlay(world, bb_europe, how='intersection')
europe.crs = {'init': 'epsg:4326'}

base = europe.plot(facecolor='lightgray')
gdf_europe.plot(ax=base, marker='o', color='red', markersize=5, alpha=0.01);

Q4: Is there a seasonal pattern in the attacks of the Allied Forces against Germany (e.g. winter vs. summer)?

In [11]:
df_noa["season"] = df_noa["month"]
df_noa.loc[((df_noa["season"] == 12) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 1) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 2)),
            ["season"]] = "winter"
df_noa.loc[((df_noa["season"] == 3) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 4) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 5)),
            ["season"]] = "spring"
df_noa.loc[((df_noa["season"] == 6) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 7) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 8)),
            ["season"]] = "summer"
df_noa.loc[((df_noa["season"] == 9) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 10) |
            (df_noa["season"] == 11)),
            ["season"]] = "autumn"
seasonal_pattern = df_noa["season"].value_counts()
seasonal_pattern = seasonal_pattern.sort_index()
seasonal_pattern.plot.pie(y='', title = "Seasonal Pattern of attacks on Germany",autopct="%1.1f%%")

df_airpl_bomb = df_airpl["Attacking Aircraft"].notnull() ### wir filtern Nan heraus und boole kommt heraus
df_airpl_bomb = df_airpl[df_airpl_bomb] ### hier machen wir aus dem booleean einen Datensatz ohne Nan mit dem wor weiterarbeiten können
carried = df_airpl_bomb.groupby("Aircraft Series")["High Explosives Weight (Tons)"].sum().sort_values(ascending = False) ## Wie viel wurde pro flugzeugtyp abgeworfen
noa = df_airpl_bomb.groupby("Aircraft Series")["Attacking Aircraft"].sum().sort_values(ascending = False) 
noa =noa[noa!=0] ### Filtern raus, was null ist
ten_most_dangerous = (carried / noa).nlargest(10) ### Wie viel wurde pro Flugzeug, nicht pro geflogenem Angriff abgeworfen?
ten_most_dangerous.plot.bar()

import geopandas as gpd
from shapely.geometry import Polygon
world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
poly_europe = gpd.GeoSeries([Polygon([(-27,33), (45,33), (45,73.5), (-27,73.5)])])
bb_europe = gpd.GeoDataFrame({'geometry': poly_europe})
bb_europe.crs = {'init':'epsg:4326'}
bb_europe

europe = gpd.overlay(world, bb_europe, how='intersection')
europe.crs = {'init': 'epsg:4326'}

year = [1940, 1941, 1942, 1943, 1944, 1945]


def where_and_when (airplane):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(22,10))      ### erstellt schonmal die vorlage für den plot

    for i, y in enumerate(year):      ### enumerate um 2 werte zu haben (gibt den jahren indizes)
        all_years_airplanes = df_airpl.loc[(df_airpl["year"]==y) & (df_airpl["Aircraft Series"]==airplane)].copy() ## Arbeitskopie des Originaldatensatzes anlegen      ### copy() sonst warnungen
        all_years_airplanes.Country.replace(np.nan, "not known", inplace=True)       ### ersetze nan-werte durch `not known`sonst bias
        ax = fig.add_subplot(2,3,i+1)      ### (rows, columns, index (starting at 1) )
        base = europe.plot(ax=ax, facecolor="lightgray")       ### Setze die Europakarte als Basis für die Kartenerstellung
        all_years_airplanes.plot(ax=ax, categorical=True, column="Country", markersize=0.5, legend = True) ### plottet alle jahre
        ax.set_title(f"In Year {y}, with Airplane {airplane}", size=14)      ### titel für die einelnen plots
    return
where_and_when("A36")
